🌱🍅🥔🐄 Calhan High School students now have a 𝗻𝗲𝘄 educational option to choose from - Agricultural Education. The 4-year course is a combination of classroom instruction, FFA, and Supervised Agricultural Experience (SAE). We couldn’t be more excited about this new hands-on learning pathway! #TheCalhanChoice #CalhanComesBack

shared_text:
Ranchland News
August 31 at 5:33 PM ·

A new 4-year course of education started recently at Calhan High School. It is the brainchild of Heidi Sellers who is the school’s agriculture instructor and FFA advisor. The program, called Agricultural Education, has three pathways, including horticulture science, animal production and ag power structure and technical systems. The last track is a rapidly growing segment of agriculture, says Sellers. It includes advocating for agriculture.

Picture 1: Sadie Taylor, Sophie Waugh, Dale Drew, Natalie Hlatki, Kaitlyn Armes, Ethan Parker, Antone Sellers and Wyatt Chamblin pose in front of the greenhouses used in their class.

Picture 2: Natalie Hlatki shows off her tomato plant.

Picture 3: Wyatt Chamblin demonstrates the composter used in the horticulture class.

We're excited to share our 𝐂𝐚𝐥𝐡𝐚𝐧 𝐂𝐨𝐧𝐧𝐞𝐜𝐭𝐢𝐨𝐧 series! Each week, we will feature a teacher or staff member who helps make Calhan School District the best! Today, we invite you to get to know Tracy Borders.

𝑷𝒐𝒔𝒊𝒕𝒊𝒐𝒏: Special Education teacher at Calhan Middle School 🍎📚

𝑯𝒐𝒎𝒆𝒕𝒐𝒘𝒏: Colorado Springs

𝑵𝒖𝒎𝒃𝒆𝒓 𝒐𝒇 𝒚𝒆𝒂𝒓𝒔 𝒘𝒊𝒕𝒉 𝑪𝒂𝒍𝒉𝒂𝒏: Five years!

𝑯𝒐𝒃𝒃𝒊𝒆𝒔: Camping, going to the lake and the beach, reading, spending time outdoors fishing, hiking, and having BBQs, and spending time with friends and family. 🎣 🥾 🏖️

𝑰 𝒍𝒐𝒗𝒆 𝒘𝒐𝒓𝒌𝒊𝒏𝒈 𝒂𝒕 𝑪𝒂𝒍𝒉𝒂𝒏 𝑺𝒄𝒉𝒐𝒐𝒍 𝑫𝒊𝒔𝒕𝒓𝒊𝒄𝒕 𝒃𝒆𝒄𝒂𝒖𝒔𝒆...the staff is my family and the community is like home.

#𝑻𝒉𝒆𝑪𝒂𝒍𝒉𝒂𝒏𝑪𝒉𝒐𝒊𝒄𝒆 𝒎𝒆𝒂𝒏𝒔 𝒕𝒐 𝒎𝒆...choosing excellence and choosing to succeed.

Tracy, we are so proud to have you as part of the Calhan Schools family! #TheCalhanChoice

post_text: 👏 Let’s give a wonderful Bulldog welcome to Calhan’s newest high school social studies teacher, Robert Elder! Originally from Oregon, Robert served in the Marine Corps and earned his bachelor’s degree from Western Washington University with a dual major in history and communication studies. Robert is entering his 14th year as a teacher, with most of his time spent in rural Alaska. He likes traveling, coffee, riding motorcycles, and exploring the Colorado backcountry. We’re happy to have him here and excited for him to share his passion for history #TheCalhanChoice!

#CalhanComesBack in just 𝙛𝙤𝙪𝙧 𝙙𝙖𝙮𝙨 on Tuesday, August 18! We can’t wait to welcome back our Bulldogs to the 2020-2021 school year! 📸🤳 Capture and share your back-to-school fun on social media, tag us, and use the hashtag #CalhanComesBack. Remember to make your posts public so we can see and share your excitement. We are looking forward to a great school year in Bulldog country! ✨⭐ #TheCalhanChoice
